    • Method Detail

      • calcEnthalpy

        public double calcEnthalpy​(double temp)
        Calculates the difference in enthalpy of a gas when temperature changes from the reference temp to the temp of interest. Since the latent heat is only known at one temperature, we have to exploit the path-independant properties of enthalpy. Calculates the enthalpy change to go from ref temp to boiling point as a liquid, and then from boiling point to actual temp as a gas. Ignores pressure effects. gaseous species are ideal gasses.
        Specified by:
        calcEnthalpy in class Species
        Parameters:
        temp - the temperature in K
        Returns:
        the enthalpy in J/mol
